description: Dawn Patrol Report for North LA: Modest scale NW swell mix hanging on this morning as a little, steep angled SSE swell starts to join in. Top combo exposures out west are running knee-waist high+, while other areas are weaker. Winds are light NNE for clean to textured surface conditions. Tide bottoms out at a 2' low at 6:40am, then rises towards a 4.6' high at 12:15pm, slowing surf down some mid day.Short-Term Forecast: Surf size holds fairly steady through the day, while light westerly winds develop for the afternoon. Tide backs out to a draining .1' low at 7:15pm.
